benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

covered: Valid Deletion: Positive path covered (TC01, TC02, TC15).
Non-Existent Resource: Tenant-not-found scenario results in 404 and no deletion (TC06).
Authorization: Missing header and invalid token scenarios covered (TC03, TC04).
Error Handling: System error during deletion (TC09).
Regression/Referential Integrity: Deletion removes catalog versions and references (TC12).
Edge Cases and Validation: Header validation (TC07, TC11, TC14) and handling of extra headers (TC08).
Large Dataset / Performance: Deletion of many versions with performance consideration (TC10).
gaps: Soft Deletes: No tests to distinguish hard vs soft delete semantics.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or burst handling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
Concurrency: More robust multi-threaded stress testing not covered.
Non-Existent Catalog within existing tenant: not specifically tested beyond tenant-not-found (TC06) or tenant-with-no-versions (TC05).
recommendations: Add a test for soft-delete semantics (hard vs soft delete flags).
Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover RBAC authorization scenarios.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure protection against bursts.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers on DELETE responses.
Add more extensive concurrency tests (higher parallelism) to ensure atomicity and consistency.
Add tests for edge cases around existing tenants with data vs no data and orphaned references, beyond TC12.
